item.caption: CT Low Dose Lung Screen (2024-01-13 1:21 PM EDT)

paragraph.content: IMPRESSION:
1. Mild coronary artery calcification
2. No acute findings.
RECOMMENDATIONS:
1. Continue annual screening with low dose CT in 12 months.
Please note that CT lung screening does not replace the need for smoking
cessation.
WSN: PLATJCDG4
INDICATION: Lung cancer screening, >= 30 pk-yr current smoker (Age 55-80y)
Cigarette smoker F17.210, nicotine dependance, cigarettes
COMPARISON: None
TECHNIQUE: Multiple contiguous LOW DOSE CT images through the lungs were
acquired without intravenous contrast. Coronal and sagittal standard
reformats were calculated. Axial maximum intensity projection (MIP) images
were also calculated. This CT exam was performed using one or more of the
following dose reduction techniques: Automatic exposure control,
adjustment of the mA and/or kV according to patient size, and/or use of
iterative reconstruction technique.
IMAGE QUALITY: Satisfactory, of diagnostic value.
SIGNIFICANT PATIENT REACTION: None
FINDINGS:
THYROID:No nodules.
LYMPH NODES: No pathologically enlarged noncalcified thoracic lymph nodes
are present.
MEDIASTINUM/HILA: Absence of IV contrast limits assessment of potential
lesions within the hila. Mediastinum is unremarkable.
CORONARY ARTERY CALCIFICATIONS: Mild amount of coronary artery
calcifications are appreciated.
AORTA: Aorta show a normal caliber.
HEART AND REMAINING THORACIC VESSELS: Unremarkable.
PLEURA: There are no pleural effusions.
LUNGS: There are no noncalcified pulmonary nodules or suspicious pulmonary
mass. Minor foci of scarring are seen in the upper right
CHEST/MUSCULOSKELETAL: No suspicious osseous lesions are seen.
UPPER ABDOMEN: Visualized upper abdomen is unremarkable.
OTHER: N/A
ASSESSMENT: Lung-RADS Category 1: (Negative) No nodules and definitely
benign nodules.
